node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'How to Manage Your Day Presented by @investinggoal ©2021 Via @kaizenexecutive'.

Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '1. Complete most important tasks first: This is the golden rule of time management. Each day, identify the two or three tasks that are the most crucial to complete, and do those first. Once you're done, the day has already been a success. You can move on to other things, or you can let them wait until tomorrow. You've finished the essential.'.

Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2. Learn to say "no". Making a lot of time commitments can teach us how to juggle various engagements and manage our time. This can be a great thing. However, you can easily take it too far. At some point, you need to learn to decline opportunities. Your objective should be to take on only those commitments that you know you have time for and that you truly care about.'.

Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3. Delineate a time limit in which to complete task. Instead of just sitting down to work on a project and thinking, "I'm going to be here until this is done, "try thinking, "I'm going to work on this for three hours". The time constraint will push you to focus and be more efficient, even if you end up having to go back and add a bit more later.'.

Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4. Do less. This is a tactic recommended by one of my favorite bloggers, Leo Babauta. Basically, do less is another way of saying do the things that really matter. Slow down, notice what needs to be done, and concentrate on those things. Do less things that create more value, rather than more things that are mostly empty.'.

Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '5. Eliminate bad habits One of the biggest time-wasters we have are our bad habits. Whether it's Netflix binge-watching, excessively surfing social media, playing games, going out frequently to drink with friends, or so on, those bad habits take away the precious little time that we do have. Use your time wisely by eliminating your bad habits if you're serious about achieving big goals in life.'.

Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '6. Find time for stillness. In our go, go, go world, too many people don't find time to just be stil. Yet, it's extraordinary what a stillness practice can do. Action and in action should both play key roles in our lives. Discovering time in your life for silence and non-motion reduces anxiety and shows you that there is no need to constantly rush. It also makes it easier to find your work pleasurable.'.

Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '7. Plan your week on Sunday. Walking into work with a plan for the week will help you focus on priorities. Cure procrastination by breaking down your weekly goals into daily tasks, so you only need a glance at this list while working. Remember to set low priority tasks by your energy and creativity levels, which may fluctuate throughout the week.'.

Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '1. Get 1% 1% Better Every Day. Most people believe that you must swing for the fences in order to achieve your true potential in any given area. James says the precise opposite is actually true; improving just 1% every day leads to dramatic results. In fact, he uses maths to prove his point. Just 1% increase every day yields a 37x improvement by the end of the year.'.

Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2. Change Your Identity To Change Your Habits. James proposes 3 layers of behavior change: (1) outcomes, (2) process, and (3) identity. In order to have six pack abs (outcome), you need to workout consistently and eat well (process), to become a man who has a six pack (identity). Another way to think about this is the "Be Do Have" model.'.

Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3. The 4 Laws of Behavior Change. He offers a step-by-step framework for not only understanding human behavior, but also how to change it. Here are the 4 steps, which he refers to as laws: >> Cue you wake up >> Craving you want to feel alert >> Response you drink a cup of coffee >> Reward you satisfy your craving to feel alert Drinking coffee becomes associated with waking up.'.

Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4. How To Workout Consistently. Using the above model, James offers some simple and powerful tips to create habits that stick. How to Create Good Habits 1. Cue- Make it obvious 2. Craving- Make it attractive 3. Response Make it easy Reward- Make it satisfying'.

Photo by Business | Entrepreneurship on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '5. How To Avoid Snacking. You've seen how to create a good habit, so let's see how to break a bad habit. How to Break Bad Habits Cue Make it invisible 2. Craving- Make it unattractive 3. Response Make it difficult 4. Reward Make it unsatisfying'.
